default7.6
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe PCC chairs the core partnership which drives forward the engagement of young people who are classified as NEETs. Talent Match is a 5-year young person led project that will engage, inspire and support 500 young people aged 18-24 from the most deprived wards in Cleveland who have been unemployed for 12 months or more.  By the end of the project, 400 young people will have improved confidence, motivation, self esteem and skills and 100 young people will be supported into employment or enterprise, sustained for 6 months or more. The Project is a collaborative approach to service delivery by the PCC,
default 
defaultPrinces Trust, Voluntary Sector, ASDA, 
defaultPD
default Ports, Middlesbrough College.
default&#xa0;
default8.0default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTransparency of and reporting by commissioners to date.default8.1
default              
defaultThe website 
defaulthttp://www.cleveland.pcc.police.uk
default 
defaultnot only facilitates a
defaultdherence to Specified Information Order
defaults but carries far more detail on the operation of the PCC. Some 1000 people visit each month. It provides an in box for those users who need further information. An independent joint audit committee is open to the public, on line ‘community clicks’ are held, a newsletter is produced and public meetings are held across Cleveland. It is disappointing that the media focus is far more likely to be on trivia than on the important work undertaken. Despite the facts being published on the website it is equally disappointing to see media reports of limited accuracy.  
default 
defaultThere are serious concerns that the desire to have some form of PCC 
defaultcomparator tables published will lead to distortion of the facts and diversion from the important issues.
default&#xa0;
default8.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe police and crime panel have been assiduous in their scrutiny of PCC actions and this has supported the genuine desire to be open. 
