default9.0default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAdditional informationdefault&#xa0;
default9.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe wider responsibilities of the PCC beyond policing can be illustrated by the drive to improve the coroners service; currently subject to unacceptable delays. A partnership with the local authority, and probation service has provided a roadmap to sustainable improvement. Reflecting on this wider responsibility, the term ‘police and crime commissioner’ should perhaps be replaced by ‘community safety commissioner’.
default9.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAchieving ‘living wage’ accreditation, especially as Cleveland has outsourced so much of its services, is a significant achievement.
default9.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIdentifying that because Home Office set firearm licence fees which do not cover costs, they require forces to subsidise licence holders. Ending this subsidy would reduce the need to cut officer numbers.
default9.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAlcohol continues to be a major driver to crime and disorder and a consequent drain on resources across the criminal justice arena. Government failure to move to minimum unit pricing could reduce pressure and assist the public sector in dealing with austerity.
